# Integration Patterns

## Supabase Edge Functions

### Silent Error Anti-Pattern (caused 3 bugs)
Always check the `{ error }` return from Supabase operations. This was missed in all 3 edge functions:

```javascript
// BAD — fire-and-forget, fails silently
await supabase.from("lead_activities").insert({ ... });

// GOOD — check and surface errors
const { error: insertErr } = await supabase.from("lead_activities").insert({ ... });
if (insertErr) console.error("Activity insert failed:", insertErr);
```

### Deployment Gotchas
- `npx supabase functions deploy <name>` **resets** the `--no-verify-jwt` flag. Always redeploy with `--no-verify-jwt` if the function is called without JWT.
- Use `npx supabase` (npm package) if the Homebrew CLI isn't installed.
- Edge functions use `import { createClient } from "npm:@supabase/supabase-js@2"` (Deno `npm:` specifier).
- Add `{ auth: { persistSession: false } }` to `createClient` in edge functions.
- `SUPABASE_URL` and `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` are auto-injected in deployed functions.

## Activity Logging Pattern

Activities (email, SMS, call, enrichment changes) persist in `lead_activities` table:

```
{ lead_id, type, performed_by, performed_by_name, metadata (JSONB), created_at }
```

- `performed_by` is nullable (FK to `auth.users`) — pass `userProfile?.id` from frontend
- `metadata` stores external IDs (Twilio SID, Resend ID) and diff data (previous/updated values)
- Frontend calls `fetchLeadActivities(leadId)` to refresh after any contact action
- Edge functions insert the activity **after** the external API call succeeds

## Enrichment Change Tracking

When contact details are updated, log both previous and new values:

```javascript
metadata: {
  previous: { email: prevEmail, phone: prevPhone },
  updated: { email: newEmail, phone: newPhone },
  changes: ["email", "phone"]
}
```

`TranslogTimeline` renders these as expandable diff entries (click to see before/after).

## snake_case ↔ camelCase Mapping

Database uses `snake_case`. App uses `camelCase`. All mapping happens in `supabaseData.js` via `leadFromRow()`, `taskFromRow()`, etc. When adding new DB columns, always update the relevant mapper function.
